<p>Now the rule:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt=" {n \choose m} = {n-1 \choose m-1} + {n-1 \choose m}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/d/f/6dff26485adf02b28675d316a258ee76.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>can be rearranged to:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt=" {n-1 \choose m} = {n \choose m} - {n-1 \choose m-1}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/2/f/d2f3aec491649afab5368a1018c22002.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>which allows calculation of the other entries for negative rows:</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>m = 0</td>
<td>m = 1</td>
<td>m = 2</td>
<td>m = 3</td>
<td>m = 4</td>
<td>m = 5</td>
<td>...</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>n = -4</td>
<td>1</td>
<td>-4</td>
<td>10</td>
<td>-20</td>
<td>35</td>
<td>-56</td>
<td>...</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>n = -3</td>
<td>1</td>
<td>-3</td>
<td>6</td>
<td>-10</td>
<td>15</td>
<td>-21</td>
<td>...</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>n = -2</td>
<td>1</td>
<td>-2</td>
<td>3</td>
<td>-4</td>
<td>5</td>
<td>-6</td>
<td>...</td>
</tr>
